        <section class="faq-section" id="offer" data-magellan-target="offer">
          <h3>About Your Offer</h3>
          <div>
            <h4>Can I work with OpenReal if I already have an agent?</h4>
            <p>You do not need an agent to sell your home to OpenReal, however, you are welcome to work with an agent and we can communicate directly with them if you prefer. If you are working with a real estate agent, you will need pay them a listing commission, usually between 1-3%.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4>Can I negotiate when I sell to OpenReal?</h4>
            <p>We focus on accuracy, not negotiation. Removing the hassle of negotiating is part of how we've simplified the process of selling your home. Our goal is to get you a market value offer on your home, which is why we ask you a lot of questions about your home before giving you an offer.</p>
            <p>If you still feel like you have more information about your home you would like us to consider, including photos of its current condition, send them our way! We would be happy to learn more about your home so we can make you the most accurate offer. Additionally, if you feel like you received an offer from us that was below market value, please tell us! We want to make sure we didn't miss something, and we'd be more than happy to share our process with you on how we came up with your offer.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4>How does OpenReal come up with my offer price?</h4>
            <p>We take pride in our method for accurately valuing homes. Our proprietary model was built by our in-house team of expert statisticians and real estate professionals. It uses all recent real estate transactions (i.e. comps in your neighborhood) to come up with an offer price. Our valuations team then takes a look at the information you gave us on your home and photos of your house to incorporate qualitative details to come up with your final offer price.</p>

            <p>If our valuations team feels like additional information is needed in order to accurately value your home, we’ll reach out for more details. Photos are particularly valuable to our team, so if we don't have photos of your home from its last listing, we'll ask you to send us some. No matter what, your home valuation and offer from us is always free!</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4>How long is the offer good for?</h4>
            <p>If you’d like to accept our offer, we ask that you respond by setting up a contract within 3 days. Once that is set up, we ask that you sign the contract within 4 days. That's at most 7 days in total between initial offer and a signed contract. However, you can always get a refreshed offer at any time. Just ask us or click the refresh button on your expired offer page and we’ll get you an offer as soon as possible.</p>
            <p>Once you sign the contract, you can choose a move-out date within 60 days. Since we buy your home directly, we're able to close on your schedule!</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4>How do I know the price is fair?</h4>
            <p>OpenReal homes are priced to appraise for a buyer. Our model takes the guesswork out of the traditional property assessment process by ensuring that a home's price is consistent with the market and transparent to buyers. We ensure that the price of a home is accurate by valuing the home based on location, characteristics and unique features.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4>How much does OpenReal charge?</h4>
            <p>Your OpenReal offer is free, and we work hard to make sure it's for the market value of your home. You can request an offer at any time – we'll always have one for you.</p>
            <p>Selling with OpenReal allows you to sell without any of the waiting and uncertainty. We take on the risk and costs you’d normally be on the hook for.</p>
            <p>If you decide to sell your home to us, we charge:</p>
              <ul>
                <li><p>2% for the OpenReal experience, which helps us take care of all the behind-the-scenes work to provide a seamless selling experience.</p></li>
                <li><p>0-5% for market risk, which varies depending on local market conditions. OpenReal allows you to sell with certainty and speed, which means we take on the risks involved with selling, such as waiting months on the market and contract fall throughs due to a buyer's financing.</p></li>
              </ul>
              <strong>What about closing costs?</strong>
              <p>Just like a traditional sale, the seller is responsible for standard closing costs including title insurance, any fees your HOA may charge, and 50% of escrow charges (we split that with you). Title insurance is a form of insurance which insures against financial loss from defects in title. Escrow charges are the fees a Title & Escrow company charges for completing the transaction. Closing costs on average total to less than 1% of your home's value.</p>
              <strong>How about repairs?</strong>
              <p>An OpenReal representative and a third-party inspector will do an inspection of your home within 7 days of the contract being signed. We’ll check the interior and exterior of your house and look for items that need repair or replacement. Additionally, we’ll make sure that what we’re seeing in person matches the information you provided us when you requested an offer and other data we used to come up with our offer.</p>
              <p>If repairs are needed, we will estimate the costs required to make these fixes and share them with you. We’ll ask that you sign an addendum to the contract that you will cover the costs of these repairs in a credit at closing. If you would prefer to do the repairs yourself, that is also an option, however we would need to reinspect to make sure they were done properly. If you aren’t willing to cover the repair costs, you are free to cancel the contract at this point and walk away without any costs or obligation.</p>
              <br>
              <p>If you have questions, we want to help! You’ll get a fast response from info@openreal.com</p>

          </div>
          <div>
            <h4>I made improvements on my home. Will that increase the offer?</h4>
            <p>If you did work on your home, we want to know! To make an accurate offer, we want all the information about the condition of your home and any improvements you made. We'll use your inputs from the questionnaire you filled to understand the upgrades you did. Additionally, you are always welcome to send us recent photos of your home, including any upgrades or renovations.</p>
          </div>

