        <section class="faq-section" id="selling" data-magellan-target="selling">
          <h3>OpenReal Selling Process</h3>

          <div>
            <h4>What happens at the final walkthrough?</h4>
            <p>A member of our team will visit your home and verify that there is not any new damage done to the property and that all personal property has been removed. It's entirely up to you if you'd like to be present. The process should only take 20 minutes or so.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4>How does closing work?</h4>
            <p>Our escrow agent will work with you to schedule a time for you to sign the closing documents. You may choose to have a mobile notary come to you, or sign at Fidelity's office.</p>
            <p>We’ll schedule a final walkthrough the day before the official close date (except Sundays, in which case you can choose a time on Saturday). On the close date, the transaction is recorded on the public record and the escrow agent distributes funds.</p>
            <p>Keep in mind, you don’t have to remember all of this right now. We’ll be right there with you all the way through!</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4>How does the inspection process work?</h4>
            <strong>Why do we do an inspection?</strong>
            <p>We provide a free inspection to verify the condition of your home before closing. A third-party inspector will check the interior and exterior of your house, including the roof, plumbing & electrical systems, and major appliances such as A/C units. Your house does not need to be empty or even tidied up for us, as long as we can easily access all parts of the house.</p>

            <strong>What if repairs are needed?</strong>
            <p>If repairs are needed, we will estimate the costs required to make these fixes and share them with you. We’ll ask that you sign an addendum to the contract that you will cover the costs of these repairs in a credit at closing. If you aren’t willing to cover the repair costs, you are free to cancel the contract at this point and walk away without any costs or obligation.</p>

            <strong>How does the inspection work?</strong>
            <p>Inspections typically take around 2 hours, depending on the size of your house. The inspector will require access to all rooms in your home, including garage, attic and basement, as well as outdoor areas such as the yard and roof.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4>How does my mortgage get paid off?</h4>
            <p>Once the contract is signed, we open an escrow account with Bell Alliance. On the final closing date (which you determine!), your escrow agent will send the payoff amount to your mortgage lender, and the remainder will be wired to your bank account.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4>How long does the process take?</h4>
            <p>Getting your offer typically takes a few hours while we analyze your home and neighborhood, though during busy times our team will sometimes take more than a day. When your offer is ready, you'll receive an email linking you to it.</p>
            <p>Since we are buying your home directly, we can close your home sale on your schedule. We can close in as little as 3 days or as many as 60, and we're flexible to change the date within this time period. You let us know your desired closing date and we will work around your schedule!</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4>What happens after I sign the contract?</h4>
            <p>Signing the contract allows us to move forward with the sale. The next step is to schedule an inspection, which you can do on your seller dashboard. We'll provide a free inspection of your property, and after that, we'll let you know the results of the inspection and we can move forward with the closing process. After that, you'll schedule a time to sign your closing documents with Fidelity National Title, and move out!</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4>When do I need to move?</h4>
            <p>You should plan to move out 48 hours before the official closing. It’s important that you have fully moved all of your belongings before we do the final walkthrough and hand over the keys. Your home doesn’t need to be professionally cleaned (we handle that!), but there should be no trash, personal items or debris left over at the final walkthrough.</p>
          </div>

        </section>

